<H3> <TI>   New European Commissioner Named, Replaces Matutes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New European Commissioner Named, Replaces Matutes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2204132194 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
22 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2204132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Marcelino Oreja Aguirre, foreign minister from 1976 
to 1979 and vice president of the European Parliament in 1989, 
will replace Abel Matutes as European commissioner now that 
Matutes will head the Popular Party's electoral list in the next 
European elections scheduled for 12 June in Spain. 
  Prime Minister Felipe Gonzalez told Jacques Delors, 
president 
of the European Commission, about Matutes' resignation. 

</TEXT>

