<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister: Spain To Join European Army </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister: Spain To Join European Army </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504201394 Madrid TVE Internacional Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504201394 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid TVE Internacional Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] The date for Spain's official membership of the 
European Army is now known; it will be 5 May. Defense Minister 
Garcia Vargas announced this today to the congress defense 
committee. The government will also study the possibility of 
increasing by one brigade to a division -- some 12,000 soldiers 
-- Spain's contribution to what has been called the Euroarmy. 
  [Correspondent R. Martinez Durban] Spain is the fourth 
country, following France, Germany, and Belgium, to form part of 
the armed wing of the WEU [Western European Union]. It already 
has some 50,000 men. Spain will initially join with the 3,400 
soldiers of the Cerro Muriano mechanized brigade in Cordoba. 
  Garcia Vargas also revealed that a low-powered ground-to-air 
SAM-7 missile from the Serb sector hit the fuselage of a Spanish 
Aviocar on 8 March as it was flying in Croatian air space. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

