<H3> <TI>   Additional Aid Granted to Former Yugoslavia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Additional Aid Granted to Former Yugoslavia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504141794 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Swedish 
1200 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Finnish Foreign Ministry has granted 
supplementary aid totaling 8.7 million Finnish markkas to the 
former Yugoslavia. The aid will be channeled via the Red Cross, 
the church's Development Aid, and the Mission's Aid to 
Developing Countries. 
  Finland has granted a total of 45.7 million Finnish markkas 
in aid to the former Yugoslavia during the past three years. 
This year's allocation was 40 million markkas before the 
supplementary allocation was granted. 

</TEXT>

