<H3> <TI>   Bjorck Criticizes UN Handling of Bosnia Force </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bjorck Criticizes UN Handling of Bosnia Force </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504171594 Stockholm Radio Sweden in English 1615 GMT 25 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2504171594 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sweden's Defense Minister Anders Bjorck is highly 
critical of the way the United Nations peacekeeping operation is 
being conducted in Bosnia. Sweden has troops there as part of a 
Nordic battalion, as well as observers. Speaking to the youth 
movement of his own Conservative Party, Bjorck said no nation 
would dream of sending 70,000 troops into the field without a 
modern, efficient command structure. He specifically called for 
a local commander able to make decisions in Bosnia under a 
mandate from the UN secretary general. 
  The Swedish defense minister said the lack of a UN force in 
and around the safe haven of Gorazde is the reason for the 
catastrophe there. His words were echoed by Sweden's Armed 
Forces Commander in Chief Bengt Gustafsson. 

</TEXT>

