<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel `Confident' of Peaceful Solution in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kinkel `Confident' of Peaceful Solution in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504124394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1128 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel said 
he is confident that a peaceful solution may be possible in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina after all, due to the most recent UN 
decisions. Priority at the moment is to remove the Serbs' 
"terrible stranglehold" around Gorazde, Kinkel said in Bonn 
today. He stressed that the agreed cease-fire is basically 
being adhered to. There is at present no reason for NATO to 
intervene. 

</TEXT>

