<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord on Return of Refugees Signed With Croatia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Accord on Return of Refugees Signed With Croatia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2504133094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1246 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2504133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Federal Interior Minister Manfred 
Kanther and his Croatian counterpart, Ivan Jarnjak, signed an 
agreement in Bonn today which makes provisions for, among other 
things, the repatriation of former civil war refugees from 
Croatia. The Interior Ministry announced in Bonn today that the 
federal states can now begin repatriation on 1 May. This 
applies to refugees who came to Germany before 22 May 1992. 
  To handle the devastation caused by the war, repatriation 
will take place in stages. Moreover, refugees from the areas of 
Croatia occupied, disputed, or devastated by the Serbs will not 
be returned until a second phase in the first half year of 1995. 

</TEXT>

