<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Newly Formed Peace Group To Visit Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Newly Formed Peace Group To Visit Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604165494 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1614 GMT 26 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604165494 </F>
<F P=104>  London PRESS ASSOCIATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new Bosnia contact group -- which is designed to 
put political "punch" into the quest for a peace settlement -- 
is to visit the battle zones soon for urgent discussions with 
the warring parties. 
  This was decided at the first meeting of the group at the 
Foreign Office in London today. It comprises representatives of 
Russia, the United States, the European Union [EU] and the 
United Nations. 
  After the meeting a spokesman said: "They agreed their 
priority was to try to restore the momentum of the peace 
process. They will explore urgently the prospects for a 
cessation of hostilities and engaging the parties in 
negotiations about a settlement. 
  ``Their work will be conducted within the framework given by 
the EU and UN and the group will travel to Bosnia shortly for 
discussions with the parties,'' the spokesman added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

