<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mitterrand Wants Immediate Conference on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mitterrand Wants Immediate Conference on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604165594 Paris AFP in English 1610 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2604165594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tashkent, April 26 (AFP) -- French President 
Francois Mitterrand, in Uzbekistan Tuesday [26 April], called 
for an immediate international conference on Bosnia, involving 
the European Union, Russia, the United States and the United 
Nations. 
  A conference proposed by Russian President Boris Yeltsin and 
supported by U.S. President Bill Clinton for next month "must 
take place but sooner, if possible immediately," Mitterrand said. 
  "The way the military conflict is taking the upper hand over 
diplomatic negotiations must not be allowed," he told a press 
conference. 
  A contact group was formed in London at ambassadorial level 
Monday to try to coordinate policy on ending the fighting in 
Bosnia. The group comprises representatives of the United 
States, Russia, the European Union and the United Nations. 
  "It is time that the great powers, together with the warring 
parties, set out an accord that it suits them to agree to," 
Mitterrand said Tuesday. 
  "The process of demanding in the name of the United Nations 
a 
retreat of Bosnian Serb military forces was very useful in 
Sarajevo. Why not continue it in the designated security zones?" 
he added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-20104 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu082aa_94004" </HT>


