<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkey's Gures Favors NATO Command of Troops in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Turkey's Gures Favors NATO Command of Troops in Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704181194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2704181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpts] General Dogan Gures, chief of the General 
Staff, has proposed that the ground forces serving in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina under the United Nations be placed under 
NATO's command. 
  The NATO Military Committee meetings, where the developments 
in Bosnia-Herzegovina were mainly discussed, have ended in 
Brussels. Gen. Dogan Gures, who attended the meetings, held a 
news conference in Brussels this morning. He pointed out that 
NATO is troubled about Bosnia-Herzegovina, and that the debates 
at the Military Committee focused on the respectability and 
prestige of the alliance. 
  ANATOLIA reports that at his news conference, Gen. Gures 
pointed out that NATO is decisive about Bosnia-Herzegovina but 
that the political decision must be made by the United Nations. 
He also said that to establish peace in Bosnia-Herzegovina, the 
air force and navy are not enough, and that the ground forces in 
that country must be placed under NATO's command even if they 
remain under UN control. [passage omitted] 
  Gen. Gures then left Brussels for Paris as the guest of his 
French counterpart. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

