<H3> <TI>   U.S. Cooperation on Submarines for Taiwan Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Cooperation on Submarines for Taiwan Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2704120094 Duesseldorf HANDELSBLATT in German 27 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU2704120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Duesseldorf HANDELSBLATT </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["sm"-signed report: "Opportunities for Submarine Order"] </F>
  [Text] Taipei -- According to information that 
HANDELSBLATT received in Taiwan, the country is to get German 
submarines through cooperation with U.S. firms. The total order 
will be in the range of 10 billion German marks [DM]. 
Apparently, the supply of submarines to Taiwan is to open the 
door for selling a German ICE [Intercity Express] high-speed 
train worth DM30 billion to the Chinese island republic. Direct 
supply of submarines to Taiwan, but not cooperation, had been 
prohibited by the Federal Security Council in Bonn. 
HANDELSBLATT has been told that the U.S. Congress is expected 
to amend the Taiwan Act in the near future to create the legal 
possibilities in the United States for supplying the submarines 
produced jointly by German and U.S. firms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

