<H3> <TI>   Government To Delay Planned Defense Cutbacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government To Delay Planned Defense Cutbacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604124194 Berlin N-TV in German 1200 GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2604124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin N-TV </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Bonn coalition meeting today put on ice the 
controversial Bundeswehr cutbacks planned by Defense Minister 
Volker Ruehe. Under pressure from Foreign Minister Klaus 
Kinkel, the meeting decided to postpone a decision and to set up 
a working party. This is to devise an alternative plan for the 
future of the Bundeswehr, based on Ruehe's proposals. Foreign 
Minister Kinkel expressed his opposition to the planned 
reduction of the armed forces to 340,000 men. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

