<H3> <TI>   Bundesbank Lowers Money Market Rates </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bundesbank Lowers Money Market Rates </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804114394 Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE in German 
28 Apr 94 p 15 </F>

<F P=103> AU2804114394 </F>
<F P=104>  Frankfurt/Main FRANKFURTER ALLGEMEINE </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["gb" report: "Money Market Rates Falling"] </F>
  [Text] Frankfurt/Main, 27 Apr -- On Wednesday [27 April] 
the German Bundesbank granted loans to the business banks at an 
interest rate of 5.47 percent within the framework of its weekly 
money market business. Last week, this so-called third prime 
rate was still 5.58 percent. Shortly afterwards the Belgian 
National Bank announced a reduction of its money market rate 
from 5.7 to 5.6 percent. Experts consider it likely that over 
the next few days other central banks in Europe will also 
slightly reduce their interest rates. 

</TEXT>

