<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delors on Bosnia Ultimatum, End of Career </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delors on Bosnia Ultimatum, End of Career </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604224294 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2200 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604224294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jacques Delors, who was the guest of Arte 
Television's Transit program this evening, said he entirely 
agrees with the NATO ultimatum given to the Serbs. The 
president of the European Commission in Brussels thinks that an 
international peace conference should be held as soon as 
possible: 
  [Begin Delors recording] As things stand now, that is what 
has to be done. Then if the Serbs have finally understood, an 
international peace conference should be organized in order to 
find a solution, which will unfortunately be based on the 
partition of the territory, which is now inevitable. 
  This is the second time I have felt ashamed in my life. The 
first time was when I ran away, walking a 500-km distance, 
running away from the German troops in 1940 during the invasion 
of my country, when there were no French troops to defend us. 
This is the second time I have felt ashamed of myself. The 
first time I was 12 or 13 years old. The construction of Europe 
gave me hope that this would all change. I am nearing the end 
of my career and I fear that I will bear this shame until the 
end of life. Yes I am ashamed! [end Delors recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

