<H3> <TI>   Ministry Welcomes Release of Chinese Dissident </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Welcomes Release of Chinese Dissident </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2504154094 Paris AFP in English 1521 GMT 25 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2504154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Paris, April 25 (AFP) -- France welcomed as a 
"positive step" Monday [25 April] the release of Chinese 
dissident Wang Juntao who was allowed to travel to New York over 
the weekend to seek medical treatment for severe hepatitis. 
  Foreign ministry spokesman Richard Duque said "we consider 
this release as a positive step and hope it will be followed by 
others." 
  Wang, 35, a journalist, was sentenced to 13 years in prison 
in 1991 for his role in China's pro-democracy movement. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

