<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Expected To Be Named Premier </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Expected To Be Named Premier </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2604163694 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1600 
GMT 26 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2604163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation, a month after the general elections, 
is that President Oscar Luigi Scalfaro has ended his 
consultations [to form a government], and Forza Italia leader 
Silvio Berlusconi is one step away from being asked to form the 
next government. Fabrizio Ferragni reports from the Quirinale 
[president's official office and residence]: 
  [Ferragni] Behind me you can see President Scalfaro, who has 
just emerged. He came here about five minutes ago to say hello 
to us -- the journalists who have been following the meetings. 
  The president made a short statement. There were no 
questions. Basically he said that he was the guarantor -- in the 
last few days the subject of guarantors has been discussed. I 
will be the guarantor of the Constitution, of the principles of 
the Constitution, and of the unity of this country, he said. 
  Scalfaro is expected to ask someone to form a government 
tomorrow morning, and it is almost certain that it will be 
Silvio Berlusconi. 

</TEXT>

