<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Wants More Time </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Wants More Time </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704185294 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 
GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704185294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Guido Dell'Anquila] </F>
  [Excerpts] It seemed as though it had all been sorted out: 
President Scalfaro was going to be a super-guarantor and was 
ready to appoint Berlusconi premier. Then problems started and 
Berlusconi has still not been asked to form a government. 
[passage omitted] 
  [Dell'Aquila] It is not Scalfaro who is 
hesitating--Berlusconi has asked for more time. He wants all 
the pieces of the jigsaw in place before he takes up the mantle, 
in order to avoid surprises. 
  There are at least two problems which still have to be 
solved. On the one hand there is the problem of 
guarantees--Berlusconi's dual role as premier and businessman. 
Yesterday, Scalfaro came forward to play the role of 
super-guarantor, but today the Northern League has applied the 
brakes. The League's Francesco Speroni has said: Berlusconi 
will be watched by us and by parliament. 
  The other problem still waiting to be solved concerns the 
much criticized plan to divide the functions of the Interior 
Ministry. However, the Northern League is sticking to its guns. 
  [Passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

