<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clarification Sought on Russian Border Closure </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clarification Sought on Russian Border Closure </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704142294 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1300 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Finland wants further clarification of Russia's 
announcement that it will close the Vaertsilae border crossing 
point for the duration of this summer. The Russian Foreign 
Ministry has announced that the border is being closed for 
construction work, which will start at the beginning of June. 
Russia estimates that the work will be completed by mid-August. 
Finland is seeking to gain further clarification about the 
closure of Vaertsilae by organizing a meeting of Finnish and 
Russian frontier delegates. 
  The Vaertsilae border crossing station near Niirala in 
northern Karelia has been kept open by mutual agreement between 
the frontier delegates. Thus far, it has not been open to 
international traffic. During Vaertsilae's closure, the Russian 
authorities recommend that goods traffic use the Uukuniemi and 
that passenger traffic use the Vartius border crossing points. 

</TEXT>

