  [Text] Spain and Sweden have called on other countries to 
contribute more UN troops to Bosnia. The call came during the 
visit of Spanish Foreign Minister Javier Solana Madariaga to 
Sweden. 
  The two countries have sent around 1,200 troops each to the 
UN protection forces in Bosnia. Solana Madariaga and Swedish 
Foreign Minister Margaretha af Ugglas say a sizeable UN presence 
is necessary in the former Yugoslavia to avoid a spread of 
