<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas: Turks Submit `Flexible Proposals' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas: Turks Submit `Flexible Proposals' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2804071594 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1930 GMT 27 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2804071594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Following his two and 
one-half hour meeting with UN special envoy Joe Clark today, 
President Rauf Denktas told journalists: We are discussing the 
issues you know about. The point is that either the amended 
document should be restored to its original form or certain 
elements that we consider satisfactory should be added to it. 
Denktas said that after his meeting with Kliridhis tomorrow, 
Clark will probably bring certain answers to the Turkish Cypriot 
side. Asked if elements satisfactory to the Turkish Cypriots 
will be added to the package, Denktas said: I do not know. We 
will see tomorrow. 
  Denktas pointed out that the UN officials are insisting on 
their proposals while the Turkish Cypriots are insisting on 
their own views. He stressed that the Turkish Cypriot side made 
certain flexible proposals during the talks and will wait for 
the results. 
  Replying to another question, Denktas said the element of 
time is still being stressed in the talks. He said: According 
to the UN officials, tomorrow is the last day, but if they see 
any encouraging signs, they will probably stay another couple of 
days. 

</TEXT>

