<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   PKK Destroy Power Lines to Northern Iraq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PKK Destroy Power Lines to Northern Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2704173494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1505 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2704173494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 27 (A.A.) -- A section of the high 
tension lines that supply electricity to the Kurds of Northern 
Iraq as part of the humanitarian aid from Turkey was bombed and 
destroyed by terrorists. 
  Foreign Ministry spokesman Ferhat Ataman told a weekly press 
conference today that the separatist terrorist organization PKK 
[Workers Party of Kurdistan] had destroyed the Silopi-Zakho part 
of the line for the second time Sunday [24 April]. 
  After destroying the line, the terrorists also set landmines 
in the region to prevent teams from repairing the line. 
  `This action against the people of Northern Iraq, should be 
a 
regrettable incident which should teach everyone a lesson,' 
Ataman said. 
  Ataman added that the line would be repaired at the soonest, 
to supply power to the people Northern Iraqis, as part of 
Turkey's humanitarian assistance to those people. 
  Ataman went on to say that ambassadors from 16 countries 
were 
called to Ankara for an evaluation meeting which will take place 
on May 4. 
  The meeting will review Turkey's relations with the West 
from 
the point-of-view of security and politics. 
  Ataman said that Turkey was placing intensive emphasis on 
the 
Iranians who were wounded during Turkey's cross-border operation 
on the terrorist camp near Zhala which is on the Iran/Iraq 
border. 
  He added that the compensation claims of Iran were under 
evaluation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

