<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman on Albanian Letter to UN Security Council </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman on Albanian Letter to UN Security Council </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2704161294 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2704161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today said 
that the letter from the Albanian permanent representative to 
the United Nations Security Council is vague and unfounded. 
  Venizelos said that this letter reminds him of the letter 
from Albanian Foreign Minister Alfred Serreqi that asked the 
United Nations to condemn Greece as a terrorist state because of 
the incident at Ano Episkopi and its friendship with the Serbs. 
  The spokesman added that, in view of the 3 May meeting in 
Zurich between Greek Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias and 
Serreqi, the Greek Government wants to be cautious about its 
statements since Greek positions are understood by the 
international community. 

</TEXT>

