<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "NATO: Italy Hosts `Dynamic Impact' </F>
Exercises"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, April 26 -- NATO forces will stage 
"Dynamic Impact" exercises in the central western Mediterranean, 
May 4-19, aimed at training convention forces to deal with 
crisis situations, the supreme headquarters of allied forces in 
Europe (SHAPE) announced today. 
  SHAPE said operation Dynamic Impact was an exercise which 
employed the use of land, sea, air and amphibious forces and 
command centers. The exercise includes naval and air operations 
in the central-western Mediterranean and land and amphibious 
operations in Italy-Friuli, Tuscany and Emilia-Romagna with the 
employment of armed forces from eleven nations -- Belgium, 
France, Germany, United States, Netherlands, Portugal, Britain, 
Greece, Italy, Spain and Turkey. 
  France and Spain, while not fully integrated into NATO's 
military structure, will participate with land, sea and air 
forces in the framework of normal training exercises with the 
allies. 
  In order to enhance security and avoid or at least reduce 
inconveniences for civil air traffic, all activities have been 
coordinated between civil and military authorities in the 
framework of the NATO Committee for European Air Space 
Coordination (CEAC). 
  Operation Dynamic Impact, will be carried out under the 
command of the new chief of allied forces in southern Europe, 
Admiral Leighton Smith. 

</TEXT>

