<F P=103> AU2604154794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Nuremberg (DPA) -- The city of Nuremberg has banned 
an election campaign rally of the radical right-wing 
Republikaner. Two counterdemonstrations in the city center, 
which had also been registered for Saturday [30 April], have 
also been prohibited. Directives to this effect were issued by 
the city's public order office on Tuesday, on the instructions 
of Nuremberg Mayor Peter Schoenlein (of the Social Democratic 
Party of Germany). Schoenlein argued that the planned rally on 
the eve of 1 May was more and more becoming an "explosive danger 
for the city's internal security and its good reputation," since 
one had to expect the rally to take a violence course. 

