<H3> <TI>   Bundesbank Releases New Figures on Money Supply </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bundesbank Releases New Figures on Money Supply </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2604085794 Hamburg DPA in German 0805 GMT 26 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2604085794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Frankfurt/Main (DPA) -- The M3 money supply rose by 
4.8 percent in March compared with the fourth quarter of 1993. 
This is a projected annual rate of growth of money supply of 
15.2 percent, the German Bundesbank announced on Tuesday [26 
April]. The M3 money supply includes cash in circulation as 
well as sight deposits, time deposits with a duration of less 
than four years, as well as savings deposits. The Bundesbank is 
aiming for a money supply growth between 4 and 6 percent for 
1994. 

</TEXT>

