<H3> <TI>   Adler Appointed Chairman of Privatized Comit Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Adler Appointed Chairman of Privatized Comit Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR2604131994 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1119 GMT 26 
Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2604131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Comit Privatization, Final Act"] </F>
  [Text] (ANSA) Milan, April 26 -- Leonello Adler, 73, was 
named the new chairman of Banca Commerciale Italiana [Comit] 
today as the curtain raised on the final act of the 
privatization of the big bank put on the block at the end of 
February. 
  The new deputy chairman and managing director is Luigi 
Fausti, and Enrico Beneduce was picked as managing director at a 
meeting of the Banca Commerciale board. 
  Earlier, former managing director Pietro Grandjacquet left 
his post and resigned [from] the boards of Banca Commerciale, 
Mediobanca and Banca Internazionale Lombarda. 
  Banca Commerciale, known as Comit, went private February 28 
when the government sold off its stake of 54 percent. 

</TEXT>

