  [Text] Madrid, April 27 (CTK) -- Spain will support 
Slovakia in its coming closer to European institutions, Spanish 
Foreign Minister Javier Solana said in a meeting with his Slovak 
counterpart Eduard Kukan today. 
  Kukan, currently visiting Spain, was received by King Juan 
Carlos I of Spain and Premier Felipe Gonzales. 
  The two foreign ministers told reporters that their views on 
international topics, including the situation in the former 
Yugoslavia, were fully identical. 
  From Spain Kukan will move to Portugal to meet with Premier 
Anibal Cavaco Silva and Foreign Minister Jose Manuel Durao 
Barroso. Kukan will also hold talks with parliament 
vice-president and the minister of trade and tourism. 

