  [Text] A Defense Ministry delegation led by Colonel 
General (Algej) Gutman, head of the Republican Headquarters of 
the Territorial Defense of the Republic of Slovenia, today 
attended the opening ceremony of the Coordination Unit of the 
Partnership for Peace in Mons in Belgium. The meeting was 
attended by the majority of the prominent NATO representatives, 
including Silvio Balanzino, deputy NATO secretary general, and 
George Joulwan. 
  In his opening speech, Balanzino said that the Coordination 
Unit of the Partnership for Peace will be the main 
communications link between NATO and the states that are 
signatories to the Partnership for Peace. It will also enable 
the assembling of individual states' programs into groups of 
projects, exercises, and training. 

