<H3> <TI>   Pact for Italy Dissidents Form New Group </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pact for Italy Dissidents Form New Group </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2804141694 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1208 GMT 
28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2804141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The expected split at the center of Mario Segni's 
Pact for Italy officially took place this afternoon with the 
presentation to the press of the Liberal Democrat Foundation by 
dissident members of the pact. Alberto Michelini, Stainano, 
Tremonti, Siciliani, and Pelanda announced their departure, a 
little after the ultimatum given to them by Mario Segni: "With 
me, or against me." 
  According to the dissidents, Segni's prejudicial opposition 
is static, while they, on the other hand, are willing to enter 
into negotiation with the government. As far as the question of 
the government confidence motion is concerned, the dissidents 
may vote against, abstain, or, if they follow their manifesto, 
vote for the government. 

</TEXT>

