<H3> <TI>   Presence in UN Mission in Mozambique To Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Presence in UN Mission in Mozambique To Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704173694 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704173694 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [Announcer] Spain has decided to prolong its 
presence in UN Operations in Mozambique [ONUMOZ] with 21 
officers from the three services after the first 20 servicemen 
end their year-long tour of duty. 
  Wednesday [27 April], the last four Spanish officers to 
finish their mission in Mozambique arrive in Madrid. At the 
beginning of March, four came back, and yesterday, 11 others 
returned. 
  The Spanish relief is already deployed in Mozambique. Just 
like the others belonging to the UN force, they are in charge of 
overseeing the peace accords between the Mozambique Liberation 
Front in the government [Frelimo] and the Mozambican National 
Resistance [Renamo] that makes up the guerrillas. 
  Fifteen Civil Guardsmen have been working alongside the 
20-odd Spanish officers for the last few days. 

</TEXT>

