<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Clark Ends Talks on Confidence-Building Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clark Ends Talks on Confidence-Building Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Atun: Turkish Cypriots Showed Goodwill </H4>

<F P=102> TA2804184094 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 28 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2804184094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Hakki Atun has stated that the 
Turkish Cypriot side did its utmost regarding the proximity 
talks on the confidence-building measures. 
  In a statement to BRT [Bayrak Radio and Television], Atun 
recalled that the Turkish Cypriot side took chances by 
displaying its goodwill when it accepted the package in 
principle so that the talks would continue. Atun added, 
however, that the advantages to the Turkish Cypriot side did not 
materialize in the package. Indicating that the Greek Cypriots 
changed the package to their favor, Atun said the Turkish 
Cypriot side's requests and concerns are always disregarded. 
  Pointing out that the UN officials asked for other areas in 
addition to Maras [Varosha], Atun stressed that it is out of 
question to accept a package which is unacceptable to the 
people, in which embargoes are not eased, and in which there are 
no concrete gains for the Turkish Cypriot side. 

</TEXT>

