<H3> <TI>   Clark Ends Talks on Confidence-Building Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Clark Ends Talks on Confidence-Building Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Turkish Foreign Minister Comments </H4>

<F P=102> TA2804181694 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 28 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2804181694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has stated 
that Turkey wants a just, permanent, viable, and realistic 
solution in Cyprus. After attending the meeting of the Islamic 
Conference Organization's Bosnia-Herzegovina Contact Group in 
New York, Cetin returned to Turkey. 
  In a statement he issued at Istanbul's Ataturk Airport on 
his 
return, Cetin said Turkey wants a Cyprus solution more than 
anybody else. Cetin stressed, however, that a solution which 
will result in reestablishing the pre-1974 hardships is not 
possible. Indicating that the leaders of the two communities 
meeting between themselves is a means toward a realistic 
solution, Cetin stated that on this issue Turkey supports the 
Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus and will continue to do so. 
Cetin further noted that there can be no question of applying 
pressure regarding this issue. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

