<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   NATO Jet Crashes After Takeoff </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NATO Jet Crashes After Takeoff </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2804152994 Paris AFP in English 1523 GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2804152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Rome, April 28 (AFP) -- A U.S. F-18 fighter-bomber 
crashed at sea Thursday [28 April] shortly after taking off for 
a surveillance flight over Bosnia from the U.S. aircraft carrier 
Saratoga, the NATO Southern Command in Naples said. 
  The plane plunged into the sea shortly after take-off. No 
details were immediately available on the cause of the accident 
in which the pilot was killed, NATO said. 
  The pilot was on his way to Bosnia to help enforce a no-fly 
zone over the territory. 

</TEXT>

