<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Renamo Leader Ends Visit, Criticizes Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Renamo Leader Ends Visit, Criticizes Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2704132394 Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network in Portuguese 
1100 GMT 27 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2704132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lisbon RDP Antena 1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Renamo [Mozambique National Resistance] leader 
Afonso Dhlakama left Portugal about an hour ago. Before 
leaving, he expressed his confidence in the role of Portuguese 
investors in Mozambique. He described the investment as 
essential to peace. Despite being pleased, Dhlakama criticized 
the Portuguese Government once more. He said the government 
should have acted sooner, and that would have prevented death 
and destruction in Mozambique. 
  [Begin Dhlakama recording] I have always criticized some of 
the Portuguese Government's attitudes. This time I told PUBLICO 
that things have changed and that is why many people died in my 
country. I have said before that if the Portuguese Government 
had understood five years ago that it was necessary for the 
sides to negotiate, it would have pressured the regime, the 
Frelimo [Mozambique Liberation Front] government, and perhaps 
only a few people would have died, and perhaps what happened -- 
the destruction -- could have been prevented. I blame the 
Portuguese Government for this. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

